{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:52:40.343Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"21573d92","input":{"summary":"Successfully performed a comprehensive accessibility and quality pass for the login portal, client portal, and admin portal. \n\nKey improvements:\n1. Document Outline and Headings: Verified exactly one clear <h1> per private workspace page.\n2. Semantic Landmarks: Upgraded the secure login portal wrapper to a semantic <main> landmark, and changed the mobile bottom and drawer navigation containers into semantic <nav> blocks.\n3. Accessible Sidebar Navigation and Menus: Appended proper ARIA descriptions (e.g. aria-label, aria-expanded, aria-haspopup) to the sidebar aside, collapsible button triggers, workspace switcher, and role switcher buttons. Configured dropdown elements to behave as semantic 'listbox' elements with individual focusable 'option' buttons.\n4. Focus States & Contrast: Added distinct focus ring visual cues (focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF]) to all interactive inputs, selectors, and CTA triggers. Verified AAA level high contrast colors across all dark enclaves.\n5. Labelled Forms and Filters: Restructured input tags in filter bars, clear buttons, and login helper forms with explicit htmlFor label bindings and descriptive screen-reader-only labels.\n6. Table and Card Interactions: Converted mobile card row divs into native focusable `<button>` elements to naturally support Enter/Space activation. Added keyboard tab navigation, focus, and Enter/Space triggers on sorting table header column cells.\n7. Accessible Dialogs & Drawers: Integrated custom ESC keydown listeners to seamlessly shut open recovery panels, secure support dialogs, command palettes, and data-table detail drawer panels. Bound overlay headings to their containers via aria-labelledby.\n8. Reduced Motion: Appended a robust global media override to app/globals.css to immediately scale down all CSS transitions, delays, and animation spins whenever is requested by the OS.\n\nRan TypeScript type-checking and linter checks; both completed with absolute zero errors. No landing page files were modified.","verified":true}}}
